" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 474px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Rest and stress positron emission tomography (PET) perfusion protocol (&lt;30 minutes)",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 454px; height: 201px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The stress agent is dipyridamole and the perfusion tracer is Rubidium-82 (Rb-82). A non-contrast computed tomography (CT) transmission scan of the chest is used for attenuation correction. The first 70-120 seconds of the acquisition are rejected to allow for clearance of the tracer from the blood pool.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     CT: Computed tomography.",
"    </div>",
